<PageTitle>About</PageTitle>

<h1>About this Snake Client (PS9)</h1>

<p>This is the student implementation of the Snake GUI client. It connects to the provided server using the assignment's line-delimited JSON protocol.</p>

<h2>Run instructions</h2>
<pre>
[From Repo Root]
chmod +x start.sh   (macOS/Linux, one-time)
./start.sh           (macOS/Linux)
start.bat            (Windows)

Then open: http://localhost:5000/snake
</pre>

<h2>Partners</h2>
<p>P1: Alex Waldmann</p>
<p>P2: George Higbie</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Use the connection box on the top-left to enter host, port, and player name.</li>
	<li>Controls: WASD or arrow keys. Key presses are sent as JSON lines like {"moving":"left"}.</li>
</ul>
